#Text=I . . . have been subjected to a disappointingly unfair process by which the Party has not even remotely provided an equal chance to other candidates and me .
#Text=I also have been subjected to a disappointingly unfair process by which the Party has not even remotely provided an equal chance to other candidates and me .
#Text=This is n't unique to the Democratic Party .

#Text=Both Parties dramatically favor their " politically privileged " member[s ] ; those individuals who have served their respective Parties for a long time and raised serious money on behalf of their Party .

column1: #Text=Perhaps that will be another legacy of this campaign as I am inclined to bring these issues to light and have the courts decide whether the practices should be continued .
#Text=That might be a greater benefit to the People than even serving as president of the United States .
#Text=Are you disappointed by the results of the primaries thus far ?

#Text=I am disappointed by the treatment I have received such as being denied the courtesy of automatic ballot access that 's afforded " politically privileged " candidate[s ] , having votes mysteriously disappear from election results , having State Parties in caucus states withhold location information , list me as " Other " and refuse to provide areas for my preference groups to form , etc.

column1: #Text=However , I am not disappointed by the results under those circumstances .
#Text=De La Fuente examines his notes during the Lesser-Known Candidates Forum .
#Text=Image : Marc Nozell .
#Text=Despite this type of treatment , I have successfully qualified to participate in the primaries and caucuses in a combination of 48 states and territories .

#Text=I have also already amassed more votes than former Senator Rick Santorum , current Senator Lindsey Graham , former Governor Jim Gilmore of Virginia , former New York Governor George Pataki and Louisiana Governor Bobby Jindal combined .

#Text=After Arizona , I passed Carly Fiorina 's vote total and I 'm rapidly closing in on former Governor Mike Huckabee 's , current Governor Chris Christie 's and current Senator Rand Paul 's vote totals .

#Text=While those candidates have suspended their campaigns , an independent NPR article recently noted my performance as somewhat of a phenomenon given that my campaign is predominantly self-funded and enjoys absolutely zero Party support or Super PAC money .
#Text=Conversely , these candidates all received massive support from the Republican Party in terms of the visibility and support they were given .
#Text=Most also have benefited from the monetary support of conservative Super PACs .

#Text=I 'm not sharing this information to brag but rather to provide a context for how the Parties have insulated themselves with a set of rules that preclude legitimate candidates such as me from having an equal opportunity to be heard and have an impact .
#Text=Why not let the People choose ?
